dekuTree.Description: Controls the behavior of Mido blocking the Deku Tree as child

csmc.Description: Modifies the chest, grass, and pot appearance so that they match their content. Works for unique items, keys, fairies, and souls. Grass and pots will otherwise always be gold if the item has not been collected

blastMaskCooldown.Name: Blast Mask Cooldown
blastMaskCooldown.Description: Changes the cooldown between each explostion of the Blast Mask

clockSpeed.Name: Clock Speed
clockSpeed.Description: Alters the speed of the clock. Some options may render seeds unbeatable due to being unable to do time-related checks

autoInvert.Name: Auto-Invert Time (MM)
autoInvert.Description: Auto-inverts time at the start of a cycle

hookshotAnywhereOot.Name: Hookshot Anywhere (OoT)
hookshotAnywhereOot.Description: Modifies all surfaces to be hooked onto and if it is expected in logic

hookshotAnywhereMm.Name: Hookshot Anywhere (MM)
hookshotAnywhereMm.Description: Modifies all surfaces to be hooked onto and if it is expected in logic

climbMostSurfacesOot.Name: Climb Most Surfaces (OoT)
climbMostSurfacesOot.Description: Modifies most surface to be climbable and if it is expected in logic

progressiveGoronLullaby.Name: MM Goron Lullaby

erBoss.Name: Boss Entrance Shuffle
erBoss.Description: Shuffle bosses either within their own game or across both

erDungeons.Name: Dungeon Entrance Shuffle
erDungeons.Description: Enable the ability to shuffle dungeons within their own game or across both.

erWallmasters.Name: Wallmaster Shuffle
erWallmasters.Description: Enables the ability for Wallmasters to take you to random locations within their own game or across both games, based on other entrance settings

erRegions.Name: Shuffle Major Regions
erRegions.Description:
- Every entrance to Hyrule Field except Market
- The entrance to Gerudo Fortress from Gerudo Valley
- The entrance to Death Mountain from Kakariko
- The entrances to the four main regions in MM
- The entrance to Romani Ranch

erIndoors.Name: Shuffle Interiors
erIndoors.Description: Enable the ability to shuffle interiors in their own game or across both games.

erWarps.Name: Shuffle Warp Songs and Soaring
erWarps.Description: Allows separate shuffling of the warp songs and soaring spots. This setting is disabled if both are selected in "Shuffle One-Way Entrances".

erOneWays.Name: Shuffle One-Way Entrances
erOneWays.Description: Enables the option of shuffling various one-way entrances.

smallKeyRingOot.Name: Small Key Ring (OoT)
smallKeyRingOot.Description: Controls the grouping of keys into key rings, for OoT

smallKeyRingMm.Name: Small Key Ring (MM)
smallKeyRingMm.Description: Controls the grouping of keys into key rings, for MM

silverRupeePouches.Name: Silver Rupee Pouches
silverRupeePouches.Description: Controls grouping of silver rupees into a single item.

openDungeonsMm.Name: Open Dungeons (MM)
openDungeonsMm.Description: Controls whether or not MM dungeons will need their respective song. Takes priority over Clear State

distinctWorlds.Name: Distinct Worlds
distinctWorlds.Description: For multiworld, with settings that involve randomness, should the worlds have distinct properties (ER, MQ, price rando...).

generateSpoilerLog.Name: Generate Spoiler Log
generateSpoilerLog.Description: Generate an extra downloadable text file with the location of every item in the seed as well as other information. It is recommended to enable this option.

probabilisticFoolish.Name: Probabilistic Foolish Hints
probabilisticFoolish.Description: If you don't know what this is, leave it ON

noPlandoHints.Name: No Plando Hints
noPlandoHints.Description: Prevents items that are part of a plando from being hinted

hintImportance.Description: Hints will tell if an item is foolish, sometimes required, or always required

cowShuffleMm.Name: Cow Shuffle (MM)
cowShuffleMm.Description: Controls whether or not playing Epona's Song near cows will give an item (MM)

shufflePotsMm.Name: Pots Shuffle (MM)

shuffleMasterSword.Description: Controls whether or not the Master Sword is shuffled

voidWarpMm.Description: In vanilla OoT, various code only checks for transitionTrigger, but in MM it also checks for transitionMode. When this is on, MM will no longer check transitionMode in those circumstances.

skeletonKeyMm.Name: Skeleton Key (MM)

magicalRupee.Name: Magical Rupee
magicalRupee.Description: Adds a Magical Rupee that can trigger every silver-rupee event.

bombchuBagMm.Name: Bombchu Bag (MM)
bombchuBagMm.Description: Turns the first out-of-shop bombchu pack you find into the bombchu bag. Has logical implications.

spellWindMm.Name: Farore's Wind (MM)

spellLoveMm.Name: Nayru's Love (MM)
spellLoveMm.Description: Adds Nayru's Love in Majora's Mask.

bootsIronMm.Name: Iron Boots (MM)
bootsIronMm.Description: Adds Iron Boots in Majora's Mask.

bootsHoverMm.Name: Hover Boots (MM)
bootsHoverMm.Description: Adds Hover Boots in Majora's Mask.

tunicGoronMm.Name: Goron Tunic (MM)
tunicGoronMm.Description: Adds Goron Tunic in Majora's Mask.

tunicZoraMm.Name: Zora Tunic (MM)
tunicZoraMm.Description: Adds Zora Tunic in Majora's Mask.

scalesMm.Name: Scales (MM)

strengthMm.Name: Strength (MM)
strengthMm.Description: Adds Goron's Bracelet, Silver Gauntlets, and Golden Gauntlets in Majora's Mask.

blastMaskOot.Name: Blast Mask (OoT)
blastMaskOot.Description: Add the Blast Mask in Ocarina of Time.

stoneMaskOot.Name: Stone Mask (OoT)
stoneMaskOot.Description: Add the Stone Mask in Ocarina of Time.

elegyOot.Name: Elegy of Emptiness (OoT)
elegyOot.Description: Add the Elegy of Emptiness in Ocarina of Time.

ocarinaButtonsShuffleMm.Name: Ocarina Buttons Shuffle (MM)
ocarinaButtonsShuffleMm.Description: Adds the Ocarina Buttons as items that are shuffled.

soulsEnemyMm.Name: Enemy Souls (MM)
soulsEnemyMm.Description: Add enemy souls into the item pool. Enemies won't spawn unless their soul is obtained.

soulsBossOot.Description: Add boss souls into the item pool. Enemies won't spawn unless their soul is obtained.

soulsBossMm.Name: Boss Souls (MM)
soulsBossMm.Description: Add boss souls into the item pool. Enemies won't spawn unless their soul is obtained.

agelessTunics.Name: Ageless Tunics

agelessBoots.Name: Ageless Boots
agelessBoots.Description: Allows Link to use boots independently of his age

agelessHookshot.Name: Ageless Hookshot

agelessChildTrade.Name: Ageless Child Trade

erMinorDungeons.Description: If turned on, it means Bottom of the Well, Ice Cavern and Gerudo Training Grounds are also shuffled

erMoon.Name: Shuffle Clock Tower with Dungeons
erMoon.Description: If paired with another dungeon shuffle, allows saving from the Quest Menu with L/C-Up while on the Clock Tower Roof.

erBeneathWell.Name: Shuffle Beneath The Well with Dungeons

erIkanaCastle.Name: Shuffle Ikana Castle Interior with Dungeons

erRegionsExtra.Name: Shuffle Market Entrance
erRegionsExtra.Description: Shuffle Hyrule Field's Market entrance among the regions.

erRegionsShortcuts.Name: Shuffle Regional Shortcuts
erRegionsShortcuts.Description:
Shuffles the various shortcuts between regions.
- Lost Woods/Goron City
- Lost Woods/Zora's River
- Zora's Domain/Lake Hylia

erIndoorsMajor.Name: Shuffle Most Interiors
erIndoorsMajor.Description: Shuffle most interiors with each other.

erIndoorsExtra.Name: Shuffle Extra Interiors
erIndoorsExtra.Description:
Shuffle additional, more complex interiors. These include:
- OOT: Link's House, Temple of Time, Windmill, Kak Potion Shop
- MM: Stock Pot Inn, Astral Observatory/Bombers' Hideout, Swamp Tourist Hut, Ikana Spring Cave

erOneWaysMajor.Name: Shuffle Standard One-Ways
erOneWaysMajor.Description: Shuffles the Gerudo Valley to Lake Hylia and Ikana Canyon to Southern Swamp entrances.

erOneWaysIkana.Name: Shuffle Ikana Castle One-Ways
erOneWaysIkana.Description: Shuffles the one-way entrances in Ikana Castle with the others. This is the keg-blocked entrance and the block moved by the switch.

erOneWaysSongs.Name: Shuffle One-Ways with Warp Songs
erOneWaysSongs.Description: Shuffles the warp songs from OOT among one-way entrances. This setting is disabled if the warp songs are shuffled with "Shuffle Warp Songs and Soaring".

erOneWaysStatues.Name: Shuffle One-Ways with Owl Statues
erOneWaysStatues.Description: Shuffles the owl statues from MM among one-way entrances. This setting is disabled if the soaring spots are shuffled with "Shuffle Warp Songs and Soaring".

erOneWaysOwls.Name: Shuffle Child Owl Flights
erOneWaysOwls.Description: Shuffle the two owl flights among one-way entrances.

erOneWaysWoods.Name: Shuffle Altered Lost Woods Exits
erOneWaysWoods.Description: Shuffle the Lost Woods entrances added by "Alter Lost Woods Exits" among one-way entrances.

players.Name: Players
players.Description: For multiworld, how many players are in the game.

triforceGoal.Name: Triforce Goal
triforceGoal.Description: The amount of Triforce Pieces that are required to win.

triforcePieces.Name: Triforce Pieces
triforcePieces.Description: The total amount of Triforce Pieces in the item pool.

preCompletedDungeonsMajor.Name: Pre-Completed Dungeons (Major)
preCompletedDungeonsMajor.Description: How many major dungeons sould be pre-completed. Can be combined with other pre-completed dungeon rules.

preCompletedDungeonsStones.Name: Pre-Completed Dungeons (Stones)
preCompletedDungeonsStones.Description: Pre-completes dungeons containing at least one stone, until it reaches that many stones. Can be combined with other pre-completed dungeon rules.

preCompletedDungeonsMedallions.Name: Pre-Completed Dungeons (Medallions)
preCompletedDungeonsMedallions.Description: Pre-completes dungeons containing at least one medallion, until it reaches that many medallions. Can be combined with other pre-completed dungeon rules.

preCompletedDungeonsRemains.Name: Pre-Completed Dungeons (Remains)
preCompletedDungeonsRemains.Description: Pre-completes dungeons containing at least one remain, until in reaches that many remains. Can be combined with other pre-completed dungeon rules.

coinsRed.Name: Red Coins
coinsRed.Description: How many Red Coins to add to the item pool

coinsGreen.Name: Green Coins
coinsGreen.Description: How many Green Coins to add to the item pool

coinsBlue.Name: Blue Coins
coinsBlue.Description: How many Blue Coins to add to the item pool

coinsYellow.Name: Yellow Coins
coinsYellow.Description: How many Yellow Coins to add to the item pool
